## STEP 1 — EKS Cluster Setup

### ❌ ERROR 1: Cluster Already Exists
```
AlreadyExistsException: Stack [eksctl-shineCluster-cluster] already exists
```
**Root Cause:** Old broken CloudFormation stack existed but cluster was never fully created.

### 🔧 FIX:
```bash
# Delete old broken stack
eksctl delete cluster --name shineCluster --region ap-southeast-2

# Create fresh cluster
eksctl create cluster \
  --name shineCluster \
  --region ap-southeast-2 \
  --nodegroup-name shine-nodes \
  --node-type t3.medium \
  --nodes 2 \
  --nodes-min 2 \
  --nodes-max 2 \
  --managed \
  --auto-mode-config-enabled=false
```
⏱️ Wait 15-20 minutes for cluster creation.

### ✅ VERIFY:
```bash
aws eks update-kubeconfig --name shineCluster --region ap-southeast-2
kubectl get nodes
```
📸 **Screenshot:** 2 nodes showing **Ready**

